<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia langcangensis" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="langcangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Begonia langcangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described and published in 1999 and its type collection was made from Fazhan He of Lancang County in Yunnan Province. Since then, no additional specimens have been collected. During our field surveys in 2010 and 2017, respectively, we did not find any plants of this taxon in the type locality and only observed 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Craib (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4104569" author="Craib, WG" journalOrPublisher="Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B7" refString="Craib, WG, 1912. Contributions to the Flora of Siam. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, Kew (3): 144-154. https://doi.org/10.2307/4104569" title="Contributions to the Flora of Siam. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, Kew (3): 144 - 154." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4104569" year="1912">Craib 1912</bibRefCitation>
: 347) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Begonia x lancangensis and its parents (B. acetosella and B. handelii) (Photos by Daike Tian) A, B male plant and female flower of B. x lancangensis C, D plant and fruits of B. acetosella E, F male and female flowering plants of B. handelii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432255" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">11C, D</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Irmsch. (
<bibRefCitation author="Irmscher, E" journalOrPublisher="Mathematische-naturwissenchaftliche Klasse" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="24 - 27" refId="B21" refString="Irmscher, E, 1921. Plantae novae sinenses, diagnosibus brevibus descriptae a Dr. Henry Handel-Mazzetti. Anzeiger der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Wien. Mathematische-naturwissenchaftliche Klasse 58: 24 - 27" title="Plantae novae sinenses, diagnosibus brevibus descriptae a Dr. Henry Handel-Mazzetti. Anzeiger der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Wien." volume="58" year="1921">Irmscher 1921</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Begonia x lancangensis and its parents (B. acetosella and B. handelii) (Photos by Daike Tian) A, B male plant and female flower of B. x lancangensis C, D plant and fruits of B. acetosella E, F male and female flowering plants of B. handelii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432255" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">11E, F</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. palmata" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="palmata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. palmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D.Don (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.86" author="Don, D" journalOrPublisher="Gale Press, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B12" refString="Don, D, 1825. Prodromus Florae Nepalensis. J. Gale Press, London, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.86" title="Prodromus Florae Nepalensis. J." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.86" year="1825">Don 1825</bibRefCitation>
). Based on the intermediate morphology of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. langcangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="langcangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. langcangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the overlapping distributions of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is hypothesised that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. langcangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="langcangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. langcangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very likely a natural hybrid of these two species. To further investigate this, by artificially crossing 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we produced, at Kunming Botanical Garden, a hybrid that was morphologically almost the same as 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. langcangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="langcangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. langcangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Begonia x lancangensis and its parents (B. acetosella and B. handelii) (Photos by Daike Tian) A, B male plant and female flower of B. x lancangensis C, D plant and fruits of B. acetosella E, F male and female flowering plants of B. handelii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432255" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">11A, B</figureCitation>
). Therefore, we confirmed that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. langcangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="langcangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. langcangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a natural hybrid. It is very similar to the hybrid (unpublished) in the same section of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. silletensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="silletensis">B. silletensis</taxonomicName>
subsp. 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="subsp. mengyanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="subSpecies" species="silletensis" subSpecies="mengyanensis">mengyanensis</taxonomicName>
Tebbitt &amp; K.Y.Guan (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3393252" author="Tebbitt, MC" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="133 - 136" refId="B38" refString="Tebbitt, MC, Guan, KY, 2002. Emended circumscription of Begonia silletensis (Begoniaceae) and description of new subspecies form Yunnan, China. Novon 12 (1): 133 - 136, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3393252" title="Emended circumscription of Begonia silletensis (Begoniaceae) and description of new subspecies form Yunnan, China." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3393252" volume="12" year="2002">Tebbitt and Guan 2002</bibRefCitation>
), which has hairy stems and petioles and larger leaves (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.17520/biods.2017050" author="Tian, DK" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="654 - 674" refId="B42" refString="Tian, DK, Li, C, Tong, Y, Fu, NF, Wu, RJ, 2017. Occurrence and characteristics of natural hybridization of Begonia in China. Biodiversity Science 25 (6): 654 - 674, DOI: https://doi.org/10.17520/biods.2017050" title="Occurrence and characteristics of natural hybridization of Begonia in China." url="https://doi.org/10.17520/biods.2017050" volume="25" year="2017">Tian et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
